 The inputs used for crop production include seed, 
 measured in kilograms; three (material that makes plants grow better) inputs: urea, 
 TSP, and an grouped (material that makes plants grow better) input of other 
 (material that makes plants grow better)s used, all in kilograms; an grouped 
 chemical input in kilograms of active ingredient per 
 hectare; grouped labor input in man-days; and 
 crop-watering/rinsing with water in hours per crop. Output data for the 
 model is yield in kilograms per hectare for each 
 crop. These values also were decided/figured out from the 
 data collected from the farmer interviews. A more 
 described/explained description of the data is included in Llewelyn (1995). 
 Data for the moving backward analysis are also from the 
 farmer interviews. Farmers were questioned (related to/looking at/thinking about) age, education and farm size. Education was 
 recorded as elementary school (6 years or less), 
 junior high school (9 years), and high school ( 12 
 years). None of the farmers interviewed had attended 
 (after high school) education. Farm size is recorded in 
 hectares of land operated, both owned and rented. 
 The (number or thing that changes) for (length of time at work or in power/right to permanent employment) is measured in terms of the 
 percentage of land owned (i.e. zero to 100). (getting involved with different types of things; not sticking with only one thing) was measured using the Herfindahl index 
