 where P; is the proportion of the farm land 
 involved in a particular business/project. A value approaching 1.0 points to/shows (focusing on doing one thing very well) whereas smaller values reflect increasing (getting involved with different types of things; not sticking with only one thing). For this sample, values ranged from 0.405 to 1.0 in the rainy and 
 middle seasons and from 0.337 to 1.0 in the dry 
 season and averaged 0.919, 0.879, and 0.814 for the 
