 5. Factors connected with inefficiency 
 A changed moving backward or tobit model is used in 
 each of the above multiproduct situations to test 
 the factors connected with technical inefficiencies. 
 The Tobit moving backward defined in Eq. (11) is guessed 
 using the Tobit procedure in TSP Version 4.2B (TSP 
 International, 1993 ). (wasting very little while working or producing something) measures are moved backward on age, farm size, percent of owned land, a 
 (getting involved with different types of things; not sticking with only one thing) dummy (number or thing that changes), and two dummy 
 (numbers that change/things that change) representing education levels. Results for 
 rainy season watered farms are presented in Table 4. 
 In the rainy season, farmers' age shows a significant quadratic relationship with all three measures of 
 (wasting very little while working or producing something). (wasting very little while working or producing something) increases with age, then eventually decreases. Also, (getting involved with different types of things; not sticking with only one thing), represented by the Herfindahl index described in Eq. (12), 
 is shown to have a significant relationship with 
 technical (wasting very little while working or producing something). The value of the guessed coefficient is positive, pointing to/showing that greater (focusing on doing one thing very well) in production is related to higher relative 
 
 (wasting very little while working or producing something). As (getting involved with different types of things; not sticking with only one thing) increases and more 
 crops are grown, (wasting very little while working or producing something) declines. It is possible 
 that the increased inefficiency with (getting involved with different types of things; not sticking with only one thing) 
 may be short-lived as farmers improve their ability to 
 grow new crops. Both the age and (getting involved with different types of things; not sticking with only one thing) 
 (numbers that change/things that change) are (meaningful numbers) at a = 0.05. 
 High school education is found to be related significantly in a positive way with total/totally/with nothing else mixed in technical and 
 scale (measures of output versus waste/getting more with less waste) at a = 0.1 0. A (related to studying numbers) relationship is not found to exist between education and 
 overall technical (wasting very little while working or producing something). All of the other (numbers that change/things that change) 
 are (related to numbers) not significant for any of the (wasting very little while working or producing something) indices. 
 In the middle season, age again is related significantly to (wasting very little while working or producing something) (Table 5). However, the (getting involved with different types of things; not sticking with only one thing) (number or thing that changes) is found to be connected only with 
 scale (wasting very little while working or producing something), with greater (getting involved with different types of things; not sticking with only one thing) leading 
 to lower scale (measures of output versus waste/getting more with less waste). Also, the dummy (number or thing that changes) 
 for high school education is found to be significant 
 at a = 0.10 for the equation with total/totally/with nothing else mixed in technical 
 (wasting very little while working or producing something). No other (numbers that change/things that change) are (meaningful numbers). 
 The results for the dry season are just like those 
 of the rainy season, as found in Table 6. Farmers' 
 age again shows a (meaningful numbers) quadratic 
 
